                        distillation. They also learn how to identify the
                        characteristic aroma of the extracted oils.<br><br>
                        Materials required:<br>
                        • Essential oil distillation apparatus<br>
                        • Flowers or leaves (for example, lavender, rosemary, or
                        eucalyptus)<br>
                        • Distilled water<br><br>
                        Procedure:<br>
                        1. Place the flowers or leaves in the distillation flask
                        of the essential oil distillation apparatus.<br>
                        2. Add distilled water to the flask until it covers the
                        plant material.<br>
                        3. Heat the flask using a heat source and wait for the
                        steam to distill the essential oil from the plant
                        material.<br>
                        4. Collect the essential oil in a separate flask or test
                        tube.<br>
                        5. Smell the extracted essential oil to identify its
                        characteristic aroma.<br><br>
                        Observations:<br>
                        • Steam is produced by heating the plant material with
                        water.<br>
                        • The steam is collected in a separate flask or test
                        tube, which contains the extracted essential oil.<br>
                        • The essential oil has a characteristic aroma.<br><br>
                        Result:<br>
                        • Essential oils are extracted from flowers or leaves,
